<doc id="827693" wikidata="Q420202" url="?curid=827693" title="Propargyl chloride">
<text>Propargyl chloride is an organic compound with the formula HC2CH2Cl. It is a colorless liquid and a lacrymator. It is an alkylating agent that is used in organic synthesis.

== See also ==
* Allyl chloride
* Propargyl
* Propargyl alcohol

